"script": "Every sheet of paper you've ever touched began as a tree boiled into soup. First, logs are stripped of their bark and ground into tiny wood chips. Then those chips are cooked in chemicals until they break down into a wet, mushy pulp. And this pulp is sprayed onto a giant moving screen, where the water drains away. Next, the soggy mat is squeezed between heavy rollers and dried over scorching hot drums. Finally, it's pressed flat and wound into rolls the size of cars, before being sliced into the pages you'll one day crumple and throw away.",
